" width=288 height=118 border="0"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwubaogoldenarmz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/02 3:11:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=75>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif" align=absmiddle>  hmmmmm ...</span><hr size=1> &quot; It seems to me, though, that you all would be happy about the possibility of having more options for your characters, rather than being 'stuck' using two weapons.&quot;<br>
<br>
Hey, it's Absor. Neat.<br>
<br>
Variety is good, certainly. But please have the people developing some of these changes keep in mind how limited a scope a warrior's choice in weapons already is due to their need to keep the monster's attention while the group proceeds to assault the monster and its friends.<br>
<br>
Also keep in mind the huge difference between a warrior's damage output and other melee's he may be grouped with at the time, like those sneaky rogues whistling nonchalantly behind the monster while the warrior with the big pink hat and multi-colored gaudy armor is making mom jokes at the monster to keep it &quot;occupied.&quot;<br>
<br>
That's all.<br>
<br>
-Wu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 266<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/02 3:11:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=76>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_eyes.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: &quot;There's a lot...&quot;</span><hr size=1> Repost from FoH board:<br>
<br>
I really don't see how making shields &quot;useful&quot; (i.e. add avoidace to them, instead of just mitigation- which is effectively softcapped, stats, or resists) is a negative for warriors at all. It basically adds options to the regular cookie-cutter endgame MT warrior, without affecting or imbalancing the non-MT warrior at all. <br>
<br>
That's not to say that there aren't issues with warrior class balance, but that's another thread (and a blurb later in this one  ). The big &quot;oops&quot; I can see happening would be making pal/sk useable shields with high avoidance on them, which WOULD make things worse/more imbalanced- how about a bit of oversight and forethought verant? Don't put mods on existing shields, and for heaven's sake don't make any of them monk-useable unless they weight 100lbs. Or better yet, make it a skill modifier and give the base skill to warriors. (i.e. for pal/sk, skill 0 + 20%mod still = 0). <br>
<br>
As far as using a shield reducing the MTs damage output, I really don't see that as being a big problem either... most of the damage a MT does is because of damage shields (no hate generated) anyway, and aggro for most end-game mobs is VERY proximity based. It's all basically upside, unless I'm missing something? <br>
<br>
Just as an aside, if/when warriors do get some tweaking, I really hope it ISN'T in the damage output area. I'd much rather see the classes strengths improved (hp, mitigation, avoidance) rather than it's secondary traits. Adding in block (maybe as a much needed innate skill at level 45?!), some type of melee stun resistance, making AC/mitigation work, a nice hefty increase in hp (or decrease/elimination of all/all 100hp 0.0 weight items), improved taunt functionality (taunt = hate increaser if fail, top of aggro list if successful), etc. Leave the mega DPS for the classes that are made for it, and make the penalty they pay for it appropriate. <br>
<br>
Just my $.02 of course. <br>
RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubrutultarewmarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brutul Tarew Marr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slayer of Whiners</span><br>  Posts: 722<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/02 3:13:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=77>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.blackcompany.cc/member_pics/45.jpg height=185 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Shield of the Slain Unicorn...</span><hr size=1> I don't think warriors would have an issue with giving up a lot of dps for better mitigation.  The block skill would obviously be a huge boon to warriors, or any tank class, and damage mitigation on a shield would be very nice as well.  It does no good however, if we can't hold aggro as well or better than we do now. If there is no aggro-increasing buff given to warrior shields, then this is a huge upgrade to all shield users, (my level 9 druid on test was blocking up a storm with an uber shiny brass shield last night)  and near useless to warriors due to the fact that we currently have no method of holding aggro other than weapon damage and procs, and the fact that there are very few warrior-useable shields in the game, and no high end ones that I know of.  <br>
<br>
If this change were accompanied with a number of new warrior-only shields with outstanding stats and a way to keep aggro as well or better than we can now, I think most warriors would welcome the option of using a shield and &quot;going defensive&quot; or dual wielding for more damage.  Without a lot of new shields added to loot tables and a way to generate aggro while using one (I like the idea of a permenant horrifying visage-like effect, that stacks with enchanter buffs of course), this upgrades everyone *except* warriors, which I hope was not the intention. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6629>Brutul Vilesilencer</a><br>

